      ],
      "text": "\n**Summary:** Yes, there are significant mechanical issues affecting Phantom Airlines operations, with 90 mechanical disruptions impacting 474 flights and costing nearly $5 million across the entire dataset.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n- **90 mechanical disruptions** have affected **474 flights** with a total reported cost of **$4,985,832**\n- Each mechanical disruption averages about 5.3 flights impacted, indicating these are substantial operational issues\n\n**Common Mechanical Issues & Fixes from Maintenance Knowledge Base:**\n\nBased on the maintenance service logs, the most frequently documented mechanical issues and their standard fixes include:\n\n- **ATA 32 (Landing Gear) Issues:**\n  - **Problem:** Landing gear indicator light illuminated\n  - **Fix:** Gear cycled, light extinguished (standard troubleshooting procedure)\n  - **Problem:** Nose wheel steering feedback unit failures\n  - **Fix:** Unit replacement followed by system testing\n\n- **ATA 29 (Hydraulic Power) Issues:**\n  - **Problem:** Hydraulic system B quantity low\n  - **Fix:** Added fluid, verified no leaks found\n\n**\u26a0\ufe0f WARNING HIGH PRIORITY:** The $5M cost from mechanical disruptions represents a significant financial and operational impact. The frequency of landing gear and hydraulic issues suggests these systems may need enhanced monitoring or preventive maintenance scheduling.\n\nThe maintenance knowledge base shows these are recurring issues with established repair procedures, indicating well-documented troubleshooting protocols are in place.\n",
